1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,720
 I think that's such a beautiful way of summarizing what Christmas is all about.

2
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:09,340
 That one line, "Born is the King of Israel."

3
00:00:09,340 --> 00:00:13,140
 Because really in that line it summarizes the culmination of what the Christmas story

4
00:00:13,140 --> 00:00:17,440
 is, this idea that Jesus has indeed come.

5
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:22,100
 That this King of Israel is not just the King of Israel, but is the King for all of us,

6
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:24,720
 for all people, for all time.

7
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:32,040
 And because the Christmas story is this declaration that indeed Jesus has come, there is this

8
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:35,320
 inherent challenge within the Christmas story.

9
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:39,280
 I don't know if you've thought about this challenge before, but think about it like

10
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:41,120
 this.

11
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:48,160
 Christmas is this idea that God has indeed stepped into this world towards us.

12
00:00:48,160 --> 00:00:55,820
 The question Christmas asks us is whether we have stepped forward towards Him.

13
00:00:55,820 --> 00:01:01,840
 He has come, born is the King of Israel, but have I come?

14
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:06,000
 Have I drawn near to Him?

15
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:12,240
 In this way it's fascinating because the Christmas story is essentially a story about movement.

16
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,960
 It's a story about a journey.

17
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:21,080
 It's a journey of invitation for all of us to come towards the one who was indeed born

18
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:28,640
 some 2,000 years ago in Bethlehem, in that stable, in the story that we all know so well.

19
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:32,840
 Will we journey to Jesus?

20
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:38,520
 I mean stop for a moment and think about the way that journey as a theme is so central

21
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:40,120
 to the original Christmas story.

22
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:45,720
 In fact, the whole story is presented to us as a journey.

23
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:51,400
 There we have Joseph and Mary in Nazareth having to take that journey from there all

24
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:56,120
 the way down to Bethlehem, a journey that would have taken them about three weeks, a

25
00:01:56,120 --> 00:02:00,800
 journey that was difficult and challenging as a journey itself, but then add to the fact

26
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:03,320
 that Mary is heavily pregnant.

27
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:08,200
 And then when they arrive in Bethlehem, there's no room for them in any of the places and

28
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:13,440
 homes in that town, so suddenly they default into a stable.

29
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:17,280
 I mean that's a considerable journey.

30
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:22,440
 And then just as we've been singing in the First Noel hymn, the journey of course of

31
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,160
 the shepherds.

32
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:28,680
 They're in the fields, aren't they, standing there and suddenly this company of heavenly

33
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:31,400
 hosts opens up before him.

34
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:37,480
 And all of these angels begin to sing out that cry, "Glory, glory, glory to you.

35
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:38,840
 Glory to God on heaven."

36
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:44,800
 And the angels say, "Don't be afraid because I've got great news for you, that in Bethlehem

37
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:49,000
 one has been born who is the King of Israel."

38
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:53,200
 And the shepherds then have a choice.

39
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:58,640
 Do they take that great news, keep it to themselves and stay where they are or are they willing

40
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:00,580
 to take a journey?

41
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:03,240
 And for them, their journey is different to Joseph and Mary.

42
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:06,320
 Joseph and Mary's journey was dangerous.

43
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:12,160
 For the shepherds, their journey was sacrificial because they had to leave behind their sheep.

44
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:16,960
 They didn't have backup shepherds hiding just in the field over, calling the backup shepherds,

45
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:19,760
 look after the sheep whilst we go look at this baby.

46
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:23,460
 If they were going to take the journey to Jesus, they would have to leave their livelihood

47
00:03:23,460 --> 00:03:24,460
 behind.

48
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:27,480
 That's a considerable sacrifice for them to make.

49
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:33,440
 And the story tells us that the shepherds leave behind their sheep, journey to Bethlehem

50
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:38,680
 and see the one who is being called the King of the Jews.

51
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:44,360
 And then also in the first Noel, we sung about the Magi, these wise men from afar who also

52
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:50,200
 take a journey, following that star that was in the sky every step of the way, traveling

53
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:55,920
 as the Bible tells us from a far away land, willing to go all of that distance to find

54
00:03:55,920 --> 00:04:05,120
 the one that now is being declared the Messiah for the world, the Magi on a journey to Jesus.

55
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:08,120
 So the Christmas story is presented to us with a challenge.

56
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:13,920
 Are you going to be like Mary and Joseph, like the shepherds, like the Magi, will you

57
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:17,200
 journey towards Jesus?

58
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:24,040
 And if Christmas is a story of journey, every journey has a starting point and a destination.

59
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:29,600
 And in many ways, the Christmas story is presented to us in the Bible as the culmination, the

60
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:35,240
 end point of one journey and the beginning point of a brand new journey.

61
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:37,480
 Let me just talk to that real quick.

62
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:41,640
 The way that the birth of Jesus is brought to us in Scripture is presented to us as the

63
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:47,240
 culmination of everything that the Old Testament had taught and longed for.

64
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:52,760
 It was the full stop, the ending of the Old Testament story.

65
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:54,840
 And we know that story well.

66
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:59,920
 Adam and Eve created in the image of God, created in communion and relationship with

67
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:05,640
 God in the garden, and then sin entering into the conversation as Adam and Eve disobey and

68
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:08,840
 take the fruit of the tree that they were not allowed to take.

69
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:12,280
 And in the reality of that sin, they realize that they have broken their relationship with

70
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:16,400
 God and they hide from Him, ashamed of what they have done.

71
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:21,760
 But God in His mercy and His grace appears in the garden towards them and comes alongside

72
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:25,680
 of them despite the reality of the choices that they had made.

73
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:30,440
 And yet what we begin to see in the biblical picture early on is that there is now a separation

74
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:35,120
 to a degree between the intimacy that was found in the garden and the reality of what

75
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:38,980
 sin does between humanity and God.

76
00:05:38,980 --> 00:05:44,120
 And really the Old Testament story is a story of a people wanting to get back into that

77
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:49,080
 relationship with God, but not understanding how to do it.

78
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:53,800
 Realizing that their sin consistently keeps them apart from the one that they want to

79
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,800
 be with.

80
00:05:54,800 --> 00:06:01,600
 And what you see throughout the Old Testament journey is God not giving up on His people.

81
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:06,000
 God coming to appear to them in different ways.

82
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:11,480
 So you have Abraham who's called by God to leave his people behind and start a new nation.

83
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:16,140
 You've got God appearing to His people in the burning bush, Moses, having this intimate

84
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:17,600
 connection with Him.

85
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:23,640
 God, then up in a mountain far away, calling Moses to come up and be in the mountain face

86
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:25,200
 to face with Him.

87
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:29,000
 And this beautiful relationship that is formed there and the giving of the law and God's

88
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,080
 character to the world.

89
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:37,520
 And then God as that pillar of fire and as that movement throughout the Exodus journey

90
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:40,780
 where they go from the place of the desert into the promised land.

91
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:45,320
 And then God meeting them in the creation of the temple and His presence falling in

92
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:48,080
 the temple and bringing His glory to His people.

93
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:52,160
 The whole Old Testament narrative is God saying, "I long to be with you."

94
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:57,120
 But what you see every step of the way is that there is still a distance.

95
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:59,240
 There's still a separation.

96
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:02,720
 It doesn't really feel like God is with us in the fullness of what He could be.

97
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:05,280
 This doesn't feel like the intimacy of the garden.

98
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:07,160
 There's a bush burning.

99
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,240
 There's a mountain on fire.

100
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:12,300
 There's a temple with a curtain pulled before it.

101
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:15,040
 There's still somewhat of a separation.

102
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:18,800
 And as you get towards the end of the Old Testament, what the people are crying out

103
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:23,880
 for is that reconnection in a way that has never been felt before.

104
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:30,200
 And they begin to realize that the only way that connection could happen is if God Himself

105
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:33,640
 acted on their behalf.

106
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:38,320
 And so it's interesting because the prophets begin to speak of this day, this day when

107
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:43,560
 God will act, when He will come and do what He's never done before, where He will bring

108
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:46,840
 His intimacy to humanity like never before.

109
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:50,960
 And do you want to know how they begin to prophetically picture it?

110
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:57,040
 They begin to speak about a child, a poor, defenseless, vulnerable child.

111
00:07:57,040 --> 00:08:04,000
 And they begin to picture that God is going to act one day to come to us in such intimacy,

112
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:07,560
 it'll be like He comes to us like a child.

113
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,400
 Isaiah says these words himself.

114
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:15,880
 He says, "Oh, the Virgin will be with a child and the Virgin will give birth to a son and

115
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:22,260
 we will call Him Emmanuel because it will be God with us."

116
00:08:22,260 --> 00:08:24,480
 And then just a little bit later, he says these words.

117
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:28,640
 He says, "For the people right now, we're walking in darkness, but then there will be

118
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:33,160
 a great light on those living in the land of the shadow of death.

119
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:35,880
 Now a light has dawned."

120
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:39,260
 And he says, "For to us, a child will be born.

121
00:08:39,260 --> 00:08:44,760
 To us, a son is given and the government will be on His shoulders and He will be called,"

122
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:50,320
 listen to this, "wonderful, counselor, mighty God, everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.

123
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:55,480
 Of the increase of His power and peace, there will be no end.

124
00:08:55,480 --> 00:09:00,560
 He will reign over David's throne and over his kingdom, establishing and upholding it

125
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:03,400
 with justice and righteousness.

126
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:06,560
 For the zeal of the Lord Almighty will accomplish this."

127
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:09,920
 The prophets begin to say, "A moment will happen.

128
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:11,720
 Just hold on a little bit longer.

129
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:19,680
 A moment will happen where it will be like God steps into this world like a child."

130
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:22,880
 And then for 400 years, there's silence.

131
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:30,560
 No prophets, no voices of hope, no nothing until this moment where the angels break open

132
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:35,760
 in the skies and speak to the shepherds and say, "This has happened.

133
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:38,080
 The day that you've been longing for has happened.

134
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:43,960
 I've got good news for you because in the town of Bethlehem, a Savior has been born

135
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,960
 to you."

136
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:49,440
 And the shepherds take that journey to meet with Jesus.

137
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:56,160
 The birth of Jesus absolutely is the end of a story, the end of the longing of God's people

138
00:09:56,160 --> 00:10:01,200
 for God to act in a way that would save them from sin and release them back into intimacy

139
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,880
 with Him forever.

140
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:05,920
 That's the birth of Jesus.

141
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:10,720
 But as much as it is an end of a story, it is also the beginning of one.

142
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:16,760
 Because from this moment onwards, Jesus begins to redefine what humanity looks like.

143
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:21,940
 He begins to speak about a new era that has begun because of Him.

144
00:10:21,940 --> 00:10:25,000
 He calls it the kingdom of God.

145
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,840
 And He begins to speak of the hope and the glory and the wonder of what it might be to

146
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:31,360
 be a new humanity caught up in this kingdom.

147
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:35,740
 He speaks about the fact that He will be able to forgive sin and that that brokenness that

148
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:41,080
 had separated humanity in the garden would be redeemed through Him and in relationship

149
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:42,080
 with Him.

150
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:48,600
 He had the audacity to forgive sin publicly, something that only God could do, establishing

151
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:53,840
 for His people His Messiahship and His divinity.

152
00:10:53,840 --> 00:11:00,640
 And then the cross, the pain of death, and then the empty tomb, and the wonder of new

153
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:06,920
 life, and then the power of the Holy Spirit being poured out on God's people, and the

154
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:08,880
 story takes off.

155
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:15,680
 And from that moment onwards, every human being in history is invited into that story.

156
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:22,280
 The risen Jesus with forgiveness and glory and hope moving towards His people.

157
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:28,600
 Oh yes, Christmas is the story of God who has come to us.

158
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:36,120
 The question is, is it also a story of us going to Him?

159
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:42,280
 I want you to think about that for a moment and maybe reflect for yourself how you might

160
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:44,560
 feel this particular Christmas.

161
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:51,400
 Here on Christmas Eve, tomorrow as we celebrate Christmas Day, what journey are you on?

162
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:55,080
 Are you drawing near to Jesus?

163
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:59,960
 Maybe for some of you in this room, that's a brand new idea.

164
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:03,960
 Maybe someone's invited you to be here today, maybe a friend or a family member, and you're

165
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:08,240
 here and you're hearing about some of these things for the first time, or maybe this is

166
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:12,080
 one of the only times that you've ever set foot in a church.

167
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:17,560
 If that's the case, I want to encourage you that this Jesus who was born on the day that

168
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:21,600
 we're celebrating here tonight and tomorrow and the one who went to that cross and rose

169
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:26,760
 again is here for you, for your journey.

170
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:30,920
 And for some of you in this room, that journey is right at the start.

171
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:35,640
 Maybe you're thinking to yourself, "I want to know more about this.

172
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,360
 I want to be drawn towards this Jesus.

173
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:40,960
 I want to know the fullness of what human life could feel like.

174
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:43,880
 I recognize that my life's not quite how I want it to be."

175
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:49,840
 And if that's you, I want to encourage you this Christmas to just take one simple step

176
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:56,480
 toward that journey, to just say in the quietness of your heart even tonight, "Lord, if you're

177
00:12:56,480 --> 00:13:01,360
 real, I'd love to get to know you.

178
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:03,040
 Would you reveal yourself to me?"

179
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:07,300
 I guarantee you that any time we ever pray that prayer to God, "God, would you reveal

180
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:08,460
 yourself to me?"

181
00:13:08,460 --> 00:13:11,640
 He will never not answer that prayer.

182
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:15,660
 So maybe for some of you tonight, that's the first step of your journey.

183
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:19,920
 But I would imagine there's maybe others of us here tonight, and maybe you've been very

184
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:25,420
 close in relationship with Jesus in the past, but there's been a time where you've drifted.

185
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:29,240
 Maybe you recognize that there's now some distance between you and God.

186
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:33,060
 Maybe that's a distance that you've created, or maybe it's one that you feel like God has

187
00:13:33,060 --> 00:13:34,360
 created.

188
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:37,540
 But for whatever reason, you feel like you're far from Him.

189
00:13:37,540 --> 00:13:39,420
 It's not as in Him as it used to be.

190
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:42,320
 It feels like it's drifted.

191
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:46,060
 That's you, and I want to encourage you that this Christmas could be the start of a new

192
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:52,760
 journey for you as well, a journey where you take that step back towards Christ, and He

193
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:55,060
 will run towards you.

194
00:13:55,060 --> 00:13:59,300
 That beautiful picture in the parable of the prodigal son, a father with his arms outstretched,

195
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:04,700
 running towards his son who is returning back to Him.

196
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:09,340
 Maybe for some of you tonight, that's the journey before you.

197
00:14:09,340 --> 00:14:14,180
 But I would imagine for most of us here, if we are Christians, if we know Jesus, if He

198
00:14:14,180 --> 00:14:18,160
 is our Lord and Savior, you might be thinking, "Well, what journey do I need to be on?"

199
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:19,300
 Let me tell you this.

200
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:22,700
 There is always something more of Jesus to be beheld.

201
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:27,740
 There's always something more of His love to be experienced, something more of His grace

202
00:14:27,740 --> 00:14:29,940
 to be encountered.

203
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:31,700
 I want to say this also.

204
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:37,140
 I think, and I'll say this personally, there's always something more of me to give Him.

205
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:41,780
 I recognize that I haven't given Him my all at times, and sometimes I've held something

206
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:44,100
 back and not fully brought myself.

207
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:48,860
 There's always something more of Him to discover and always something more of me to give.

208
00:14:48,860 --> 00:14:54,300
 So maybe for most of us, the journey this Christmas that is the challenge before you

209
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:58,620
 is are you willing to lean in that much more in your relationship with Jesus?

210
00:14:58,620 --> 00:15:02,220
 Are you willing to pursue Him even more?

211
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:06,540
 Paul, writing to the church in Ephesus, would say, "My desire for you is that you would

212
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:09,980
 attain to the whole measure of the wholeness of Christ."

213
00:15:09,980 --> 00:15:11,820
 There's always more.

214
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:15,580
 Will you come?

215
00:15:15,580 --> 00:15:22,580
 So Christmas absolutely is a journey, and that journey is before all of us.

216
00:15:22,580 --> 00:15:25,700
 God has moved towards us.

217
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:30,340
 The question for you is are you moving towards Him?

218
00:15:30,340 --> 00:15:31,340
 Can I pray for us?

219
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:32,340
 Let's pray.

220
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:36,100
 Father, I thank You for the people here tonight.

221
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:42,900
 Those that are online watching, we are so grateful that we can gather around these carols

222
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:47,820
 and liturgy and Your Scripture tonight with this great hope that is found in the birth

223
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:49,300
 of Jesus.

224
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:55,940
 Lord, we come before You tonight grateful that You've stepped into our world, that in

225
00:15:55,940 --> 00:15:59,700
 the incarnation of Christ, You've drawn near to us.

226
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:01,820
 What a gift.

227
00:16:01,820 --> 00:16:08,420
 And Father, the challenge there for us to ask ourselves, are we drawing near to You?

228
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:13,300
 Lord, I want to pray for anyone here tonight where this might be the first time that they've

229
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,700
 heard such an idea.

230
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:20,980
 And maybe in their hearts tonight, they're saying, "Yeah, I don't know it all.

231
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:21,980
 I don't have all the answers.

232
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:28,580
 I'm not even sure if this is fully real, but I'm willing to give it a shot."

233
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:31,420
 God, would You reveal Yourself to me?

234
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:35,500
 Maybe for some of you, You can make that simple little prayer tonight.

235
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:42,340
 Father, I just ask that You would reveal Yourself more to me.

236
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:46,620
 Maybe if you've drifted a little bit tonight and you know that your relationship with Jesus

237
00:16:46,620 --> 00:16:52,220
 is not what it used to be and not what you want it to be, you're also invited on a journey

238
00:16:52,220 --> 00:17:00,220
 afresh to come to a Father who runs towards you, not in anger or not in punishment, but

239
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:05,500
 with open arms, putting that ring on your finger, that coat on your back, reinstating

240
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:10,500
 you to the fullness of a son and a daughter.

241
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:17,940
 So for some of you tonight, maybe your prayer is, "Lord, I'm here again, and I know I've

242
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:22,580
 been distant, but can we start again?

243
00:17:22,580 --> 00:17:27,420
 I want to be with You again."

244
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:32,260
 And then finally, for those of us tonight where maybe we plateaued in our relationship

245
00:17:32,260 --> 00:17:38,020
 with Jesus, where it's just become a thing that we've gotten used to, and we love Him,

246
00:17:38,020 --> 00:17:42,260
 and we know that He loves us, but there's not any vibrancy.

247
00:17:42,260 --> 00:17:46,100
 It's just kind of plateaued a little bit.

248
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:53,820
 My prayer for you tonight is that you would know the joy of rediscovery, the joy of finding

249
00:17:53,820 --> 00:17:56,380
 afresh your relationship with Him.

250
00:17:56,380 --> 00:18:00,740
 So Lord, I pray for anyone tonight where that is their journey tonight.

251
00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:06,340
 Lord, would You reveal Yourself in even more glorious ways, and would the mystery of You

252
00:18:06,340 --> 00:18:09,660
 forever be in front of them?

253
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:14,200
 So Lord, whatever it might be, thank You for coming to us.

254
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,720
 We now come to You.

255
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:18,720
 We pray this in Jesus' name.

256
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,140
 Everyone says, "Amen."

